info.name: Fade For Google
info.description:
Fade For Google is inspired by Fade for Youtube by Macsy (https://userstyles.org/styles/141088/fade-for-youtube)  When i saw that, i immediately fell in love, and i thought: "Hey, a google version would look nice"
So i made one!
info.additionalInfo:
Instructions for the google theme (With the google theme, it will also show up on "newtab"
1. Download this folder: https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1dYP6IKA-b0vFl9J23d3RdAz2RYFAezRE?usp=sharing
2. If you are on chrome (which you should be) click on the 3 dots on the upper right corner of your screen
3.Click "More tools"
4.Click "Extensions"
5.Enable developer mode (upper right corner)
6.Click "Load unpacked"
7.Select the folder
8.Enjoy!

Update! So apparently the google theme doesnt work on some devices (it worked on my chromebook) so sorry if it doesnt work on your device!
